  "text": "In this paper we have restricted ourselves to comparing the field content of the deformed coset models and non-critical superstrings. It remains to see whether or not the BRST cohomologies of both models are related. For bosonic W N -strings this relation has been shown to exist [10, 11, 12] and thus one expects a similar result for the supersymmetric string models (see ref. [CITATION_1] for an analysis of the osp(1|2) case). There are many other questions that remain open in the relation between the G/G cosets and string theories. For example, one would expect to have a current algebra prescription to compute correlation functions in non-critical string theories. Another problem that, in our opinion, deserves future investigation, is the relation between the G/G BRST symmetry and the topological symmetry of non-critical strings discovered in ref. [34] (see also [35] ).",
